처음하는 것처럼 방심하지 않고 다시 시작해보겠습니다.
민사법 둘 중 한 과목은 수석을 하고 싶네요
JUST DO IT!

안녕하세요! 법무사 시험을 준비하는 꾸준맨 부맨입니다.
이전에는 장교(ROTC 출신)로 해병대에 6년간 몸담았고, 전역 후 그간 배워보고 싶었던 영상 편집, 코딩, IT(네트워크, 정보보안 등) 여러가지를 공부 했습니다. 그러던 중 좋은 기회를 만나 쿠팡 자회사인 CFS에 입사. 물류센터에서 근무를 했습니다. 군인시절부터 조직(회사)에 의지 하지 않아도 되는 내 능력으로 내 삶을 살고 싶다는 생각을 자주 했고, 경제적으로 독립한 전문가(장인)가 되고 싶었습니다. 

군대 후배의 추천으로 법무사에 도전하게 되었고, 쿠팡 퇴사 후 2021년 8월 말부터 법무사 1차 공부를 시작해서, 1년 만에 집에서 인강으로 22년 법무사 1차 시험에 합격하였고, 당해 2차 시험은 130명 안에 들지 못했습니다. 23년에 2차 공부를 후회없이 하였지만 불합격했습니다. 새로운 마음으로 재동차 도전중입니다. 같이 힘내요🔥🔥🔥

22년 11월 2차 시험이 끝나고 공부가 잘 되지 않아, 2023년 새해를 맞아 스터디윗미를 해보자는 생각을 했고, 열심히 실행하고 있습니다. 항상 시작이 가장 어려운 것 같습니다. JUST DO IT!!!그래도 해보는게 중요하다고 생각합니다.

미라클 모닝, 미라클 러닝, 공부, 독서 등 스스로 동기부여하려고 노력하고 있고, 가지고 있는 좋은 에너지들을 많은 분들과 주고 받고 싶어요! 부지러너 여러분들과 같이 2024년 목표 달성 해요! 들어와서 봐주시는 분들 정말 감사합니다!

I do a real-time study with me live every day except for one day of the week. I want to motivate you as a friend who studies with you. Even though time is different, we have the same heart to strive for our dreams.

S18.title: 12 hour☘️ Study with me LIVE ☕ calm cozy ambience🩺POMODORO🔥Real-time study #Medgirl 2025-05-19 13:02
S18.description:
📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

We have a Chat bot- 🤖
Commands for chat bot- 

!hi - when you join in👋
!start - to start studying
!top - Top Points
!points -  to know your points💯
!complete - when done with the goal

Chat rules:
- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!
- Please feel encouraged to write in English so no one would feel excluded in the chat :)
- Please check YouTube's Community Guidelines
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

S37.title: 【 勉強配信｜스터디윗미｜Study With Me 】19:00~22:00｜25/5 Pomodoro 2025-05-19 13:02
S37.description:
The person who just joined us, ValoRapha, is actually a volunteer staff member at the seal rescue center in the Netherlands—the same center whose links I often share🦭
He’s originally from Germany and travels to the Netherlands every weekend to help out.
Even during his lunch breaks at work, he actively chats with viewers in the facility’s live stream chat, and he’s very kind about responding to people on social media too, often sharing adorable photos of the seals. He’s a truly wonderful person.

Some of you might have seen the live stream from the link I shared yesterday—that was Valo! Also, when I posted on X recently, inviting people to study together, he actually stopped by my live stream too. I was so happy and a little starstruck.

You might be wondering why I share links to seal live streams that don’t seem related to studying. So, here’s a bit of background: this rescue center went viral on X last summer, and many Japanese viewers started following it. I myself found the seals so comforting that I’ve been checking the live stream almost every day. Watching them swim, sleep, and return to the ocean full of energy—sometimes there are sad moments too because it’s a rescue facility—but seeing all this daily made me want to support them somehow. (Though right now I’m not working, so it’s tough to do much beyond taking care of myself…🫣)

One of my motivations for continuing daily live streams is that someday, when my channel earns revenue, I’d like to donate to this center as well as other animal protection groups, research institutions, and environmental conservation efforts. (Half of it might go toward my snacks, though… 🍩🍭)

I share various links often, but I do so with the hope that the time we spend studying together can someday help support places like this. I’d be really grateful if you could understand that and look on warmly.

Sorry for the long message! Let’s keep doing our best studying together!

this channel isn’t just for studying; 

I've been there; I almost killed myself at a railway and stopped studying for half a year, it would be easy to just give up and let life win, but instead I use my situation to drive myself forward even when i dont fucking feel like it.

It can get overwhelming sometimes, especially if like me you have no one to talk to, but if you and me are studying together we've got eachother. Lets get through this together :)

mental health stuff:
due to severe mental health issues I don't talk during my streams in the breaks, its because I go through a lot of shit in my life and I dont want to ruin other people's days by putting negative energy out there. Instead I try to record videos as much as I can where I'm just talking about life stuff, hopefully these videos resonate with some of yall, and I'm sorry I can't talk during the stream I promise it will get better.

✨ Mehnat aisi karo ki success bhi soche — 'Yaar, isse toh milna hi padega!'
✨ Success is not final, failure is not fatal: It is the courage to continue that counts. — Winston Churchill
✨ The harder you work for something, the greater you’ll feel when you achieve it.
✨ Don't stop when you're tired. Stop when you're done.
✨ Doubt kills more dreams than failure ever will. — Suzy Kassem
✨ Push yourself, because no one else is going to do it for you.
✨ Dream big. Work hard. Stay focused.
